I"Ÿ<h1 id="navigation">Navigation</h1>

<p>The navigation supports especially only one level. If you need deep nested structures you propably should use a larger documentation system like <a href="https://www.gitbook.com/">GitBook</a>.</p>

<h2 id="adding-a-page-to-navigation">Adding a Page to Navigation</h2>

<p>Not every page by default is part of the navigation. If you want to add a page to the navigation you have to add the <code>navigation</code> attribute with a desired <code>index</code>:</p>

<pre><code>---
layout: page
title: Navigation
navigation: 2
---
</code></pre>

<p>The navigation <code>index</code> is starting with 1 representing the first item.</p>
